\subsubsection{Base Chance}

Often this will be equal to some multiple of a characteristic of the
Adept. The characteristic is taken at its current value, multiplied
appropriately, and then other modifiers are added.

\subsubsection{Difficulty Factor}
d936 1
d941 2
a953 18
\subsubsection{Extended Rituals}
\label{magic:extendedrituals}

Some rituals require a far greater investment of time than the
standard one hour, possibly requiring weeks or even months.  It should
be noted that rituals extending for periods of 24 hours or more do not
require the intense concentration of ordinary rituals.  The Adept is
working and perhaps supervising the work of others, but is not
involved in constant concentration.  The Adept may eat, sleep (8 hours
a day) and perform other activities requiring less than 2 hours a day
while engaged in a lengthy ritual.  During the period of an extended
ritual an Adept can utilise only stored magic, and that inherent in
the ritual.  Note that these restrictions may mean that an Adept will
lose practice in skills or weapons while performing an extended
ritual.  Adepts may use 1 week during an extended ritual as 1 day of
training time.  Magic cannot be trained during this time.  If the
Adept dies during an extended ritual, the ritual fails completely.

